This paper is about cracking ciphers using a machine learning approach, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of GANs, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as language modeling and text generation, which are relevant to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses image processing techniques to visualize the results, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV).
